f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_340/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 340w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_490/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 490w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_645/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 645w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_740/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 740w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_965/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 965w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1165/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 1165w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1315/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 1315w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1465/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 1465w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,g_center,pg_1,q_60,w_1600/ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h.jpg 1600w\"></p></div></span></p><figcaption>Photo: Drew Angerer (Getty Images)</figcaption></div><span data-id=\"ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h\" data-recommend-id=\"image://ix3nabfwzjepfchc0z1h\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"6485\" data-height=\"3640\" data-lightbox=\"true\" data-recommended=\"false\"></span></figure><p>Facebook has pushed back against Apple’s planned rollout of anti-tracking tools at <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://gizmodo.com/facebooks-new-ad-campaign-tries-to-remind-you-that-targ-1846354304&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://gizmodo.com/facebooks-new-ad-campaign-tries-to-remind-you-that-targ-1846354304\">every</a></span> <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.wired.com/story/sorry-facebook-ios-changes-not-bad-for-small-businesses/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.wired.com/story/sorry-facebook-ios-changes-not-bad-for-small-businesses/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">possible</a></span> <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://gizmodo.com/facebooks-latest-strategy-throw-apple-under-the-bus-1844729984?rev=1616121621809&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://gizmodo.com/facebooks-latest-strategy-throw-apple-under-the-bus-1844729984?rev=1616121621809\">opportunity</a></span>, but now the social media giant seems to be <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://twitter.com/swodinsky/status/1372692528143667200?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1372692528143667200%7Ctwgr%5E%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&amp;ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fkinja.com%2Fajax%2Finset%2Fiframe%3Fautosize%3D1id%3Dtwitter-1372692528143667200&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://twitter.com/swodinsky/status/1372692528143667200?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1372692528143667200%7Ctwgr%5E%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&amp;ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fkinja.com%2Fajax%2Finset%2Fiframe%3Fautosize%3D1id%3Dtwitter-1372692528143667200\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">changing its tune</a></span> in a last-ditch effort to save face. On Thursday, CEO Mark Zuckerberg said Facebook may actually be in a “stronger position” after the privacy updates to iOS and is optimistic about how the company will weather this change, according to <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.cnbc.com/2021/01/28/apples-b.html&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2021/01/28/apples-b.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">CNBC</a></span> and <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.cnet.com/news/facebook-ceo-mark-zuckerberg-criticizes-apple-on-clubhouse/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.cnet.com/news/facebook-ceo-mark-zuckerberg-criticizes-apple-on-clubhouse/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">CNET</a></span>.</p><p>“The reality is is that I’m confident that we’re gonna be able to manage through that situation well and we’ll be in a good position,” he said in a Clubhouse room Thursday per the outlets.</p><p>With Apple’s planned privacy updates for iOS 14, which are scheduled to roll out <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.cnbc.com/2021/01/28/apples-b.html&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2021/01/28/apples-b.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">sometime this spring</a></span>, the company aims to give iOS users more transparency and control over their data by requesting permission before apps can track their activity across other apps and the web.</p><div><div data-vjs-player=\"true\" id=\"188551\" poster=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,fl_progressive,pg_1,q_80,w_470/niesrtmtpbs0xyzmcn8k.jpg\" playsinline=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" lang=\"en-us\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Video Player\" data-caption=\"[]\"><video id=\"vjs_video_3_html5_api\" preload=\"auto\" muted=\"muted\" playsinline=\"playsinline\" poster=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fit,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_470/niesrtmtpbs0xyzmcn8k.jpg\"></video><p><span>Video Player is loading.</span></p><div dir=\"ltr\"><p><span role=\"presentation\">Current Time&nbsp;</span><span aria-live=\"off\" role=\"presentation\">0:00</span></p><p><span role=\"presentation\">Duration&nbsp;</span><span aria-live=\"off\" role=\"presentation\">-:-</span></p><p><span role=\"presentation\">Remaining Time&nbsp;</span><span aria-live=\"off\" role=\"presentation\">-:-</span></p></div></div><div><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Permalink meta&quot;,&quot;Author click&quot;,&quot;https://kinja.com/caitlinmcgarry&quot;]]\" href=\"https://kinja.com/caitlinmcgarry\"><div><p><img alt=\"\" data-srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media