g.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_739,pg_1,q_60,w_1315/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 1315w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_824,pg_1,q_60,w_1465/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 1465w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_900,pg_1,q_60,w_1600/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"30px\" draggable=\"auto\" data-chomp-id=\"cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-alt=\"\" data-anim-src=\"\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,fl_progressive,g_center,h_80,pg_1,q_80,w_80/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 80w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_78,pg_1,q_60,w_140/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 140w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_149,pg_1,q_60,w_265/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 265w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_191,pg_1,q_60,w_340/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 340w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_275,pg_1,q_60,w_490/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 490w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_362,pg_1,q_60,w_645/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 645w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_416,pg_1,q_60,w_740/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 740w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_542,pg_1,q_60,w_965/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 965w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_655,pg_1,q_60,w_1165/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 1165w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_739,pg_1,q_60,w_1315/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 1315w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_824,pg_1,q_60,w_1465/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 1465w, https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/c_fill,f_auto,g_center,h_900,pg_1,q_60,w_1600/cpl1gunivlw6jhqta5o9.jpg 1600w\"></p></div></a></div></div><p>Facebook hasn’t been too keen on that idea given that roughly <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.google.com/search?lei=XuU3YJfJGNaWwbkPnPW_qAc&amp;q=instagram%20revenue&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiX8I69zoXvAhVWSzABHZz6D3UQsKwBKAN6BAgxEAQ&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.google.com/search?lei=XuU3YJfJGNaWwbkPnPW_qAc&amp;q=instagram%20revenue&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiX8I69zoXvAhVWSzABHZz6D3UQsKwBKAN6BAgxEAQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">98% of its revenue stream</a></span> depends on targeted ads, which are built around monitoring a person’s browsing habits. The company <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://gizmodo.com/facebooks-new-ad-campaign-tries-to-remind-you-that-targ-1846354304&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://gizmodo.com/facebooks-new-ad-campaign-tries-to-remind-you-that-targ-1846354304\">launched a campaign</a></span> to convince folks that personalized ads are good, actually, which has so far involved taking out <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.wired.com/story/sorry-facebook-ios-changes-not-bad-for-small-businesses/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.wired.com/story/sorry-facebook-ios-changes-not-bad-for-small-businesses/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">full-page ads</a></span> in several leading newspapers to condemn Apple and running <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://gizmodo.com/facebooks-new-ad-campaign-tries-to-remind-you-that-targ-1846354304&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://gizmodo.com/facebooks-new-ad-campaign-tries-to-remind-you-that-targ-1846354304\">a video ad</a></span> claiming that Apple’s privacy updates are killing small businesses by not giving Facebook and other apps free rein to hoover up your data.</p><p>(As you might already suspect, Facebook’s claims <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.wired.com/story/sorry-facebook-ios-changes-not-bad-for-small-businesses/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.wired.com/story/sorry-facebook-ios-changes-not-bad-for-small-businesses/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">have been found</a></span> to be misleading at best, and self-serving propaganda at the worst. While advertising might become slightly more difficult for small businesses and developers with Apple’s new updates, Facebook stands to take <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://mobiledevmemo.com/facebook-may-take-revenue-hit-from-apple-privacy-changes/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://mobiledevmemo.com/facebook-may-take-revenue-hit-from-apple-privacy-changes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">the biggest revenue hit</a></span>, not the little guys.)</p><div data-inset-url=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/video/offers/ref=atv_hm_hom_c_wiT8hs_MDQjja_8_1?ots=1&amp;slotNum=0&amp;imprToken=c6bc1deb-f5ab-c21b-47f&amp;ascsubtag=942612b4654812e93581ae4254ae4ee47d1c3767&amp;benefitId=cbsaacf&amp;mnsid=mbnx33-20&amp;tag=kinjadeals-20\" data-inset-category=\"CommerceInsetMobile\"><p>G/O Media may get a commission</p></div><p>Now though, with Apple’s updates looming close on the horizon, Facebook is apparently adopting a new strategy: <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Corn%20Cobbing&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Corn%20Cobbing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">corncobbing</a></span>. Aka, to continue to embarrass oneself rather than admit to being brutally owned.</p><p>On Thursday, Zuckerberg reiterated concerns that Apple’s decision could still hurt small businesses and developers, but also expressed hope that Facebook might benefit from the situation, CNBC and CNET report.</p><p>“It’s possible that we may even be in a stronger position if Apple’s changes encourage more businesses to conduct more commerce on our platforms by making it harder for them to use their data in order to find the customers that would want to use their products outside of our platforms,” he said.</p><p>That’s a far cry from the bleak picture Facebook painted before. In August 2020, the company warned that Apple’s updates could lead to a <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.cnbc.com/2020/08/26/facebook-apple-ios-14-could-cut-audience-network-revenue-in-half.html&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2020/08/26/facebook-apple-ios-14-could-cut-audience-network-revenue-in-half.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">more than 50% drop</a></span> in its Audience Network advertising business, which lets mobile software developers personalize ads based on Facebook’s data. Facebook’s chief financial officer David Wehner <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.cnbc.com/2020/07/30/facebook-says-apples-ios-14-changes-could-hurt-its-ad-targeting.html&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2020/07/30/facebook-says-apples-ios-14-changes-could-hurt-its-ad-targeting.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">also expressed concern</a></span> it could hurt the social network’s ability to effectively target ads to users.</p><p>Apple and Facebook did not immediately respond to Gizmodo’s request for comments. Apple has <span><a data-ga=\"[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://gizmodo.com/apple-defends-delay-of-ios-14-feature-limiting-app-trac-1845727151&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]\" href=\"https://gizmodo.com/apple-defends-delay-of-ios-14-feature-limiting-app-trac-1845727151\">repeatedly defended its planned privacy updates</a></span> against Facebook’s accusations, arguing that these new features aren’t getting rid of targeted ads entirely but instead giving users the chance to opt-out if they wish to.</p><div><p>Subscribe to our newsletter!</p><p>News from the future, delivered to your present.</p></div></div></div>","author":"John Gruber","siteTitle":"Daring Fireball","siteHash":"fc569638025dadf22a867470f8215f38855cf50e975782a6c989909474292a36","entryHash":"b747068c2945d58700c40425aa3a1de7bc6880690bbb1ff027e7213b2360a9d2","category":"Tech"}